{
  "stem": "7069.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Slavery work condition was that we had to work in this kind of position and receive only half the wages that the normal-- normal-- the, the, the normal German citizen would receive under those circumstances.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You see, Hitler-- Hitler had drawn everybody into the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so they needed people to work in those kinds of works.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The women, by the way, were sent to factories to make ammunition, or to make or repair uniforms, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But we were there, on the street, working.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And not that the employer didn't have to pay the full wages-- he had to pay the full wages-- the only thing was, the system was as follows.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Before anything happened, out of the normal full wages, 50% of it he had immediately to take off and sent to Hitler's treasury, to Hitler's coffers.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The rest of the 50% that I received, there was first a deduction of the taxes on the whole amount, so that you can imagine there wasn't very much left-- money left over to buy things.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "On the other hand, that wasn't much of any importance because there wasn't much that you could buy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I told you, you couldn't go anyplace that cost money, to concerts or something like that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And you couldn't buy anything else, rations.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Jews, we received only half of the ration cards that the rest of the population received.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So money, there was no way that you could spend any money.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were, in my case, men out of all directions of life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, let me give you one particular scene to demonstrate how that looked.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were there, a group of people next to me was a man working, an elderly man.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
